{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:05.652095+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture of the repo. Here is a summary of what the README prescribes, mapped to each of your three goals, followed by the exact shell commands in order.\n\n---\n\n## What the README says (and doesn't say)\n\n- **The repo contains three Dart projects**: `core` (shared logic), `mobile` (Flutter app for Android/iOS), and `web` (an **AngularDart** PWA – *not* Flutter web).\n- **The README does not mention Flutter web tooling.** It only covers Flutter for mobile and AngularDart (`webdev`) for the web target.\n- **The CI script** (`.travis.yml` + `ci-script.sh`) shows the exact dependency and build commands used by the upstream project.\n\nBecause you want a **Flutter web build** with output under `build/web/` (the standard Flutter web build directory), the commands below adapt the project's own patterns to the Flutter web workflow. The mobile Flutter project at `mobile/` doesn't yet have web platform support (no `mobile/web/` directory), so enabling it is part of the process.\n\n---\n\n## Exact shell commands (run from the repository root)\n\n### 0. Prerequisite – rename the TMDB config file\nThe README and CI script both require this before anything will compile:\n\n```bash\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\n```\n\n### (a) Install Flutter web tooling\n\n```bash\nflutter config --enable-web\n```\n\n> **Note**: If your Flutter version already has web enabled by default (Flutter ≥ 2.0), this command is harmless and ensures web is active. You can verify with `flutter doctor`.\n\n### (b) Add web platform support to the mobile project & fetch dependencies\n\n```bash\ncd mobile && flutter create --platforms=web . && flutter pub get\n```\n\n- `flutter create --platforms=web .` adds the missing `web/` directory (and necessary configuration) to the existing Flutter project.\n- `flutter pub get` fetches all Dart/Flutter packages (the CI script uses the older alias `flutter packages get`; `flutter pub get` is the modern equivalent).\n\n### (c) Produce a release web build under `build/web/`\n\n```bash\nflutter build web\n```\n\nRun this from the `mobile/` directory. The release output will be at:\n\n```\nmobile/build/web/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of all commands in order\n\n```bash\n# 0. Prerequisite (required by README)\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\n\n# a. Install Flutter web tooling\nflutter config --enable-web\n\n# b. Add web support to the Flutter project & fetch dependencies\ncd mobile && flutter create --platforms=web . && flutter pub get\n\n# c. Build release web\nflutter build web\n```\n\nAfter the final command, the deployable web assets are in **`mobile/build/web/`**.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1627, "prompt_tokens": 12213, "total_tokens": 13840, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 977, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12032}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 12032, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 181}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "c26c75b2-d402-41ff-99fa-378eaedb73c6", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-533a-7bf0-b70a-8e97bae9a276-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12213, "output_tokens": 1627, "total_tokens": 13840, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 12032}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 977}}}}]}}}
